title: SIU Football Romps to 1st Conference Win
text:
SIU Football Romps to 1st Conference Win Tools 
Story Created: Oct 10, 2015 at 10:29 PM   10, 2015 at 11:44 PM CDT 
CARBONDALE-- The SIU football team was dominant from the outset of their game with Missouri State. The Salukis were desperate for their first conference win of the season and jumped out to a 21-3 lead after one quarter. The Dawgs pile up 408 yards of offense in the first half, to lead 35-9 at the break. 
Southern continued the rout in the second half, setting Saluki stadium records for yards and points, in the 73-26 win over the Bears, that improves SIU's record to (2-3) on the season.
